com.esri.mo2.cs.geom
Interface ClementiniGeometry

All Known Subinterfaces:
FeatureGeometry, MultiPoint, Polygon, Polyline
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseFeatureGeometry, BaseMultiPoint, BasePolygon, BasePolyline, Envelope, Point
public interface ClementiniGeometry

The methods in this interface implement the CBM (calculus-based methods) of Clementini et als.

Note: All methods with Clementini relationships are prefixed with clem_.

ClementiniGeometry is geometry that can be compared topologically using Clementini comparison methods. For example,

  • A Clementini geometric object has a boundary and an interior.
  • A point has no boundary, just interior.
  • A polyline (or path) has two endpoints as boundary, all points on the line between the two endpoints defines its interior.
  • A polygon has the defining lines as boundary and the interior of the polygon as its interior.

See A Comparison of Methods for Representing Topological Relationships , Eliseo Clementini and Paolino Di Felice.

See Also:
Polygon, Envelope, Point, Polyline, MultiPoint

clem_touch

public boolean clem_touch(ClementiniGeometry geometry)
Determines if a Clementini Geometry and another Clementini Geometry are touching. Touch applies to Polyline/Polyline, Polyline/Polygon, Polyline/Envelope, Polyline/MultiPoint, Polygon/MultiPoint, Polygon/Polygon, Polygon/Envelope, Envelope/Envelope, and Envelope/MultiPoint. Other relationships return false.

Parameters:
geometry - the Clementini Geometry
Returns:
a boolean variable - True or False
